laboratory_examinations.findings: Urine was ++ for protein; sediment contained 50 to 100 white cells and moderate numbers of tubular cells.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Urine was +++ for protein upon hospital admission; on the second hospital day, total urinary protein excretion was reported as 3.4 g per 24 hours.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Initial BUN was 20 mg/dL; on admission it was 40 mg/dL and increased to 98 mg/dL by the fifth hospital day.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: BUN increased progressively from 40 mg/dL to 98 mg/dL over five days.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Initially around 0.8 mg/dL; on the day of admission, it was 1.5 mg/dL; then increased from 3.7 mg/dL on admission to 7.6 mg/dL by the fifth hospital day.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Creatinine increased from 1.5 mg/dL at admission to 7.6 mg/dL over five days.

laboratory_examinations.findings: At admission: Sodium 125 mmol/L; Potassium 3.0 mmol/L; Chloride 95 mmol/L; Carbon dioxide 24.5 mmol/L.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Sodium levels fluctuated to 120 mmol/L, Potassium levels increased to 4.3 mmol/L, and Chloride decreased to 81 mmol/L by the fifth hospital day.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Hematocrit: 37.2%; White-cell count: 14,700 per mmÂ³ (Neutrophils: 66%, Lymphocytes: 11%, Eosinophils: 14%).
